    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, if the US isn't \"taking sides,\" why does it seem like they're only intervening when it benefits their own strategic interests? It feels like a convenient way for the US to frame their presence as being about \"international law\" while actually just trying to contain China's influence. Wouldn't a more neutral view say that both China and the US are just competing for dominance in the region?",
